# Workflow Rules for Exo Development

## Git Workflow
- **ALWAYS commit changes to git and push** after making code modifications
- Stage changes with `git add -A`
- Commit with descriptive messages using `git commit -m "message"`
- Push to remote using `git push origin new_main` (or current branch)

## Deployment Workflow
- **ALWAYS deploy changes** after committing and pushing
- Use `./deploy-all.sh` to deploy to all three nodes (macstudio-m4, macbook-m4, work-macbook-m4)
- Wait for deployment to complete and verify connectivity

## Debugging Workflow
- **ALWAYS check logs when failures are mentioned**
- Check logs on all three nodes when investigating issues
- Use `ssh <node> "tail -n <N> ~/.exo/exo.log"` to view recent logs
- Look for errors, exceptions, and relevant status messages
- Check logs proactively when user reports any failure, error, or issue

## Node Configuration
- Three nodes: macstudio-m4, macbook-m4, work-macbook-m4
- Logs are located at `~/.exo/exo.log` on each node
- API is available at `http://100.93.253.67:52415`
- All nodes should have ssh and sudo configured the same way
